<div class="hero">
    <h1>System Unit: Disassembly & Assembly</h1>
</div>

<div class="container">
    <div class="safety-box">
        <strong>⚠️ Safety First:</strong> Always unplug the power cord and press the power button for 5 seconds to drain static electricity. Use an anti-static wrist strap or touch a metal part of the case frequently.
    </div>

    <h2>Phase 1: Disassembly</h2>
    <p>Removing components requires patience. Never force a part if it feels stuck.</p>
    
    <div class="step-card">
        <div class="number">1</div>
        <div><strong>Remove Side Panels:</strong> Unscrew the thumb-screws at the rear and slide the panels off to reveal the internals.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="step-card">
        <div class="number">2</div>
        <div><strong>Unplug Cables:</strong> Carefully remove the 24-pin motherboard cable, CPU power, SATA cables, and GPU power connectors.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="step-card">
        <div class="number">3</div>
        <div><strong>Remove Expansion Cards:</strong> Unscrew the GPU from the case bracket, press the PCIe slot tab, and pull the card straight out.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="step-card">
        <div class="number">4</div>
        <div><strong>Extract Motherboard:</strong> Unscrew the standoff screws holding the board to the case. Lift gently, ensuring no ports are caught in the I/O shield.</div>
    </div>

    <h2>Phase 2: Assembly</h2>
    <p>Building it back is the reverse process, with a focus on cable management.</p>

    <div class="step-card">
        <div class="number">1</div>
        <div><strong>Install I/O Shield & Motherboard:</strong> Snap the shield into the case first, then align the motherboard with the standoffs and screw it down.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="step-card">
        <div class="number">2</div>
        <div><strong>Seat RAM and CPU:</strong> If not already installed, place the CPU into the socket and click the RAM sticks into their slots until they "snap."</div>
    </div>

    <div class="step-card">
        <div class="number">3</div>
        <div><strong>Connect Power Supply:</strong> Plug in the 24-pin and 8-pin cables. Route them through the back of the case for better airflow.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="step-card">
        <div class="number">4</div>
        <div><strong>Final Check:</strong> Ensure all fans are plugged in and the CPU cooler is seated firmly before powering on.</div>
    </div>
</div>

